div.p:
3. Thirdly, the middle betweene good and evill is either, 1. of meere deniall (as they terme i
                     •…
                  ) in which there is neither good nor evill to be found; and so all substances, whether they be things naturall or artificiall, are middle things or indifferent: or it is, 2. a middle of participation, which doth so far agree with both extreams, as the extreams agree betweene themselves; and thus no substances are properly things middle and indifferent by themselves, because none of them are either good or evill, but only actions, and dispositions to actions.
